            <title><![CDATA[Call Of Duty's Best Stoner DLC Yet Turns You Into A Pot-Smoking Lizard]]></title>
            <link>https://www.gamespot.com/articles/call-of-dutys-best-stoner-dlc-yet-turns-you-into-a-pot-smoking-lizard/1100-6528200/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/call-of-dutys-best-stoner-dlc-yet-turns-you-into-a-pot-smoking-lizard.1050999/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[https://www.gamespot.com/articles/call-of-dutys-best-stoner-dlc-yet-turns-you-into-a-pot-smoking-lizard/1100-6528200/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f<br/><br/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><p>
    <span data-nosnippet="">GameSpot may receive revenue from affiliate and advertising partnerships for sharing this content and from purchases through links.</span>
  </p><article itemscope="" data-type-id="1100" data-guid="1100-6528200">

            
            
  


        

  


        
        
              <section>

                  
          <div data-content-element-selector="p, .js-buylink-item-container" data-allowed-classes-selector="js-buylink-item-container">
                <p>Activision has announced what's coming to Call of Duty: Black Ops 6 and Warzone for the holiday season, and while there are <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/gallery/cod-black-ops-6-and-warzone-season-1-reloaded-includes-holiday-events-snowball-fights-and-new-zombies-map/2900-6010/" data-ref-id="2900-6010">plenty of festive updates planned</a>, one store bundle in particular stands out.</p><p>The "Dank Days" Tracer Pack is themed around one of Call of Duty's most enduringly popular activities: smoking pot. The bundle invites players to "coast through the holiday season" with plenty of weed-themed items, including the "Bongshot" Mastercraft blueprint for the KSV SMG. Intriguingly, Activision said the visual effects of this weapon "intensify" with successive kills. No footage has been released so far, but it seems like this could be in reference to some kind of "trippy" visual effects.</p><p>Also in the bundle is the "Blunty" operator skin, which turns your character into some kind of lizard. Then there's the "Blunt Trauma" LMG blueprint for the GPMG-7, as well as the "Weed Wacker" A.G.R. MK 1 scorestreak skin, in addition to the "Toke-a-Bloke" finishing move. The DLC also comes with the "Aim High" weapon reticle, the "My Bong" weapon charm," and "Pass It" spray, and the "Greener Grass" loading screen.</p><figure data-align="center" data-size="large" data-img-src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1179/11799911/4409119-dank.jpg" data-ref-id="1300-4409119" data-ratio="0.5625" data-width="1920" data-embed-type="image"><a href="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1179/11799911/4409119-dank.jpg" data-ref-id="1300-4409119"></a><figcaption>Say hello to Blunty.</figcaption><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1179/11799911/4409119-dank.jpg"></figure><p>As mentioned, the Call of Duty series has <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/call-of-duty-modern-warfare-2-will-continue-franchises-love-of-marijuana/1100-6506751/" data-ref-id="1100-6506751">featured marijuana-themed content for a long time now</a>. In 2023's Modern Warfare III, Activision brought the legendary stoners Cheech and Chong to the game as part of an event called Blaze Up. Activision even got the comedians themselves to do the voices.</p><p>For more on what's coming to Black Ops 6/Warzone Season 1 Reloaded this December, check out the gallery below.</p>
  
                        
    
        
        
  
